{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1782925323343,"sessionID":"ses_0e161b9f6ffe75vhj1ifiw59Va","part":{"id":"prt_f1ea16c4e0015RmQEaQMyPA74h","messageID":"msg_f1ea15958001rUiGfexdYvGOhC","sessionID":"ses_0e161b9f6ffe75vhj1ifiw59Va","snapshot":"6d9a7e5dacbf04e2a0140385843ff24f912f6687","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1782925327947,"sessionID":"ses_0e161b9f6ffe75vhj1ifiw59Va","part":{"id":"prt_f1ea17a21001cFaNLoz8GdQs2T","messageID":"msg_f1ea15958001rUiGfexdYvGOhC","sessionID":"ses_0e161b9f6ffe75vhj1ifiw59Va","type":"text","text":"The current evidence points to two viable implementation families: a lightweight in-process session map for same-process runtime protection, and a durable per-session state file patterned after `mk-goal` for restart/concurrency safety. I’m now materializing the requested 3-iteration packet and final synthesis.","time":{"start":1782925326881,"end":1782925327946},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0e82a7c9d43caa27016a45480edc1881919cbbb7339b66ffc2","phase":"commentary"}}}}
